        "text": "Hi Scott! Thanks for asking! There’s not much action yet. And I sorely need to provide a nice set of examples.\n\nThe best I can point out to now is:\n• On fourdata: <https:\/\/github.com\/altocodenl\/TODIS\/?tab=readme-ov-file#pillar-1-single-representation-of-data>, this is the data representation. It determines the shape of both data and code.\n• On call and response (the main paradigm): <https:\/\/github.com\/altocodenl\/TODIS\/?tab=readme-ov-file#pillar-3-call-and-response> . That text is now a bit old, because now I write the response on top (rather than below) the call, for example:\n```= 30\n@ sum 10 20```\n• The only real cell running is in the test suite, which is itself in fourdata. A lot of it is really low level (testing things like parsing), but <https:\/\/github.com\/altocodenl\/cell\/blob\/master\/test.4tx#L1167|from this point onwards> it starts to show a bit what the language looks like.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
